In his biography, An Unsuitable Boy, Karan Johar talked about being persecuted for his sexual orientation. "I have become like the poster boy of homosexuality in this country... I wake up to at least 200 hate posts," he had written.Now, in an interview with CNN-News18, Karan talked about how the never-ending speculation surrounding his personal life has left him wary. The Ae Dil Hai Mushkil director said that even an innocuous dinner with a male friend becomes front page news. "I'm afraid to go out for dinner with another man because the paparazzi reaches everywhere and if you go out for dinner with a man, you're sleeping with him. 